-- S.Korean stocks, won rise as global risk revives, Fed eyed
-- By Christine Kim
-- Mon Oct 27, 2014 02:04AM EDT
-- None



SEOUL, Oct 27 (Reuters) - South Korean shares and the won rose on Monday as upbeat U.S. earnings and economic data reduced concerns over the health of the global economy.

The Korea Composite Stock Price Index (KOSPI) <.KS11> closed up 0.3 percent at 1,931.97 points. The won <KRW=KFTC> ended onshore trade at 1,052.2 to the dollar, up 0.5 percent from Friday's close of 1,057.5, according to exchange rate data provided by Seoul Money Brokerage Services (SMBS).